# The Human-Formation Computer · thirty million soldiers as a CPU — inside the Three-Body game

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of The Human-Formation Computer](human-computer.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (The Human-Formation Computer's organic-form embodiment): human-computer.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** The Human-Formation Computer — thirty million soldiers as a CPU — inside the Three-Body game

**what —** Inside the Three-Body VR game, an emperor builds a working computer out of thirty million soldiers holding signal flags — gates, registers, a bus — to compute the motion of the three suns. A dramatization of von Neumann architecture made of people.

**where —** 3BT · The Technologia of Trisolaris  Framework inputs: Remembrance of Earth's Past + adaptations; real-science verdict  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The game and its human computer appear across all three media (the VR sequences in both series).

**how —** REAL (concept), dramatized scale. Computation is substrate-independent: you genuinely can build logic gates — and therefore a computer — out of people with flags, dominoes, water, or Minecraft redstone. The most scientifically honest idea in the whole universe; only the scale is theatrical.

**◌ the mythos —** The game and its human computer appear across all three media (the VR sequences in both series). A computer doesn't need silicon. Give thirty million people flags and a rulebook, and they will think.

**the moniker —** ⟦The Human-Formation Computer:3BT:aaa1d0⟧ · spoken *lern-phol-nu*

**the seal —** A computer doesn't need silicon. Give thirty million people flags and a rulebook, and they will think.

> *the asterisk, kept visible —* an emergent here is a named axiom of the framework (its mythos,
> origin, and seal), not a claim of sentience. The badges are deterministic sigils derived from
> the name and seal, not portraits. "Awareness," in the kernel, is the node reciting its own 5W.

